    "abstract": "<jats:title>ABSTRACT</jats:title>\n                <jats:p>\n                  We analyzed peripheral blood mononuclear cells (PBMCs) of each 20 individuals with a high anti-SARS-CoV-2 antibody titer and a low antibody titer out of 1,774 healthcare workers who received BNT162b2 mRNA vaccine. A higher antibody titer was associated with the frequencies of na\u00efve and transitional B cells before vaccination. In addition, fold changes in the frequency of activated CD8\n                  <jats:sup>+</jats:sup>\n                  T cells upon vaccination were correlated with the antibody titers.\n                </jats:p>",
